64.6	Robert_Fisk	Robert Fisk	Robert Fisk (born 12 July 1946) is an English writer and journalist from Maidstone, Kent. As Middle East correspondent of The Independent, he has primarily been based in Beirut for more than 30 years. He has published a number of books and has reported on the United States's war in Afghanistan and its 2003 invasion of Iraq. Fisk holds more British and International Journalism awards than any other foreign correspondent.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c4/Robert_Fisk%2C_Christchurch%2C_2008.jpg/220px-Robert_Fisk%2C_Christchurch%2C_2008.jpg
